---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 13
  Paragraph: 16
Title: The Way Of Heaven
---
Yao replied, "I never abuse those who have nowhere to sue, nor reject
the poor people. Grieving for the dead, comforting the orphan, pitying
the widow - I use my mind in these things alone."
